<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-25T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-25T11:36:00-05:00" n="1110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4025.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-25T10:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1912—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Zapata’s communication mentioned in my May 24, 5 p.m., has been addressed
                            to all consuls general here and the evening papers have published its
                            substance; I learned this after sending my telegram. Perfect
                            arrangements for concentration of American colony have for some time
                            been in effect. Consul General made no reply to Zapata, whose letter
                            caused but little alarm here; it is believed his forces are
                            insufficiently armed to undertake a considerable movement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>